  Locus:
    Page: 19
    Verse: 9
Tags:
  - Anger
---
Angry men are blind and foolish, for reason at such a time takes flight
and, in her absence, wrath plunders all the riches of the intellect while
the judgement remains the prisoner of its own pride.
